OpenTAP Linux Distribution   

Prerequisites:
- Ubuntu (16.04)
- .NET Core 2.0

Installation instructions for Ubuntu can be found here: https://www.microsoft.com/net/learn/get-started/linuxubuntu

Automatic installation of OpenTAP
- Run the command "sh INSTALL.sh"

Manual installation:
- Unzip the TAPLinux.TapPackage file. This is a normal ZIP file.
- Set directory permission as being read-write in the OpenTAP directory. This is 
  needed for package installation and session log output.

Usage:
The main executable is "tap". If you ran the automatic install script
this should be callable straight away. Otherwise you should call:
"dotnet tap.dll <arguments>"